node.text: Last night to sign up for the Ike Foundation Pro Am this Sat. June 5th on the Upper Chesapeake Bay! First place wins a Basscat/Yamaha valued at over 30K and all the proceeds go towards kids fishing! Sign up at theikefoundation.org or SWIPE UP in my story! @theikefoundation

node.title: Last night to sign upFor the Ike Foundation Pro Am! First place wins a Bass

node.text: I’ve had a lot of questions about the baits I used to win my first pro kayak event on the Upper Chesapeake Bay. Well here they are: I used a 5” @berkleyfishing Powerbait General in black blue flake on a @vmchooks 4/0 Ike Approved Worm Hook with a VMC 1/16 oz. nail weight in the tail. I fished this along scattered grass in and around subtle ditches. And my two big bass came on the Berkley Maxscent Creature Hawg rigged on a 3/0 VMC Heavy Duty Flipping Hook and a 1 oz. VMC Tungsten Weight. I punched this bait in thick Hydrilla Mats that had deep water right on the edge! @tacklewarehouse #ikeapproved
